frameDefinitions: A State_of_affairs is evaluated as good (or bad), against a background assumption that previously, the State_of_affairs was thought to be unlikely to occur.
The words in this frame have to do with people and the personal Relationships they are or can be a part of.
An Experiencer, Expressor, Event, or State has an emotion as brought on by an Stimulus or Topic.
This frame concerns people being in an altered mental state that is induced by an Intoxicant.
An State_of_affairs will come to hold with respect to a Protagonist at some future time.
frameExamples: And of course that drippy <t><fex name='Partner_1'>boyfriend</fex></t> of hers backed her up.
The <t>joyful</t> reunion took place on Sunday.
Exile was his <t>fate</t> and he triumphantly turned it into the fruit of his life.
listRoleDefinitions: The State of affairs that is evaluated.
The Protagonist is the one for whom the destiny is evaluated.
The <fen>Role</fen> filled by the <fen>Protagonist</fen>.
The time for which the <fen>Protagonist</fen>'s destiny is good.
The location where the <fen>Protagonist</fen> has luck.
That partner in the <fen>Relationship</fen> who is realized as the subject of verbs in active form sentences, or of adjectives in predicative uses.
That partner in the <fen>Relationship</fen> who is not expressed as the external argument.
The joint construal of both <fen>Partners</fen> in the <fen>Relationship</fen>.
The <fen>Experiencer</fen> is the person or sentient entity that experiences or feels the emotions.
The <fen>Topic</fen> is the general area in which the emotion occurs.  It indicates a range of possible <fen>Stimulus</fen>.
The <fen>Stimulus</fen> is the person, event, or state of affairs that evokes the emotional response in the <fen>Experiencer</fen>.

The body part, gesture, or other expression of the <fen>Experiencer</fen> that reflects his or her emotional state.  They describe a presentation of the experience or emotion denoted by the adjective or noun.
The <fen>State</fen> is the abstract noun that describes a more lasting experience by the <fen>Experiencer</fen>.
The <fen>Event</fen> is the occasion or happening that <fen>Experiencer</fen>s in a certain emotional state participate in.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Experiencer</fen>, <fen>Expressor</fen>, <fen>Event</fen>, or <fen>State</fen> can be described as having said emotion.
The mental state of the <fen>Cognizer</fen> is changed by an <fen>Intoxicant</fen> .
The <fen>Intoxicant</fen> alters the <fen>Cognizer</fen>'s mental experience.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Cognizer</fen> becomes intoxicated.
The <fen>State_of_affairs</fen> that is destined to occur to the Protagonist.
The Protagonist is the one for whom the future <fen>State_of_affairs</fen> is destined.
The <fen>Role</fen> filled by the <fen>Protagonist</fen> in his/her destiny.
The time for which the <fen>Protagonist</fen>'s future is determined.
The location in which <fen>State_of_affairs</fen> is destined to occur to the <fen>Protagonist</fen>.
listRoleExamples: I was rather fortunate <fex>in the late 90s</fex>, making much of my fortune at that time.
At Medicine Man's ragtime dance contest, a jubilant <fex>girl</fex> drove the crowd wild.
Earl is jubilant <fex>about his new swim trunks</fex>.
<fex>Putin’s initiative</fex> caused joyful excitement in Baku on Friday.
He met me with a glad <fex>face</fex>.
Armed officials marred the joyful <fex>mood</fex> at the recent Mon festival in Samut Sakhon.
I am helping them to have the joyful <fex>birth</fex> they want.
Deciding that his true destiny is <fex>as a healer</fex>, Henderson returns home, planning to enter medical school.
Their destiny <fex>over those years</fex> was to gradually take charge of most of the world's operations.
